title: Curves of Life: A Note Through Growth and Decay Models
text: Exponential models are among the most fundamental tools in mathematical modeling. Although real-world phenomena are often too complex to be captured by exponential models alone, requiring adjustments and the inclusion of external factors - these models still serve as essential foundations for many modern, sophisticated mathematical frameworks. This journal documents my study of the core principles of exponential models and their notable applications.

title: Thao (Tracy) Tran
text:
A data analysis master student with finance undergraduate background.
My Garden of Gains is a quiet space where I gather my thoughts and observations about the world of maths and finance. Like keeping a journal in a garden, I write to reflect on the news I read, the case studies I explore, and the insights I uncover along the way. This is where ideas take root, grow, and sometimes bloom into deeper understanding. It’s not just about gains in numbers, but growth in thought.
